Package controller

Class Manager

java.lang.Object
controller.Manager
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.fxml.Initializable
public class Manager extends Object implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
This is the manager class that controls everything. It consists of event handlers for buttons as well
Author:
dylan, raph

  • Method Details

    • loadData

      private void loadData()
      This public void method goes through the file txt database and creates a new Toy object with the information given for the toys in the file. It creates a new object depending on the kind of toy it is and it does so through Polymorphism. It then adds the toy within the array list.

    • initialize

    • searchToyType

      private void searchToyType()
      This private method searches the toy type. It creates a substitute array list type Toy that stores the matching searched toy type within this list.

    • purchase

      private void purchase(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      This private void method sets the searchErrorLabel text field as empty. It collects the selected toy from the list view and checks if the toy matches any of the toys in the original Toy array list, and then it subtracts the toy's stock by one.
      Parameters:
      event - is the event of the buy button in the search toy tab in the GUI

    • removeToy

      private void removeToy()
      This private void method will remove a toy from the database. It will require the exact serial number in order to find the toy to delete

    • searchToRemove

      private void searchToRemove(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)

      Parameters:
      event - is the event of the search button in the remove toy tab in the GUI

    • remove

      private void remove(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)

      Parameters:
      event - is the event of the remove button in the remove toy tab in the GUI
